    "description": "SOFTWARE ENGINEERING is an engineering discipline concerned with all aspects of software production, from initial requirements to system maintenance. It applies a systematic, disciplined, and quantifiable approach to the development, operation, and maintenance of software products using well-defined scientific principles and methods. This course explores the core concepts and practices essential for building efficient and reliable software systems.",
