    "is_elective": false,
    "description": "This course, Measurement and Instrumentation, provides a foundational understanding of electrical and electronic measurement techniques. It covers fundamental concepts, various types of instruments, and the principles behind calibration and error analysis, preparing students for practical applications in electrical engineering. The course emphasizes both theory and application of measurement systems.",
    "outline": [
