    "is_elective": false,
    "description": "This course, EEE 300 Electric Circuit Theory II, builds upon foundational circuit analysis techniques, delving into advanced methods like Fourier analysis and network synthesis. It covers waveform analysis, network functions, and the realization of systems with prescribed characteristics, preparing students for complex electrical engineering applications.",
