    "description": "EEE 324 (Linear Systems) provides a foundation for analyzing and designing control systems through mathematical modeling of physical systems. The course covers both linear and nonlinear systems, focusing on techniques like transfer functions, frequency response, and stability analysis. Students will explore analogues in electrical, mechanical, and thermal domains.",
