    "is_elective": false,
    "description": "This course explores the fundamental principles of electric power systems, covering generation, transmission, distribution, and economic operation. It delves into power system components, energy sources, and essential concepts like power factor correction and polyphase systems, preparing students for advanced analysis and control.",
    "outline": [
      {
        "title": "Introduction to Power Systems",
        "subtopics": [
          "Basic components of power systems",
          "National grid organization",
          "Transmission and distribution levels",
          "Nigeria National Power Grid",
          "Power system structure"
        ],
